## 2. Backend Architecture

### Pattern: Controller → Service → Repository

```
HTTP Request
    │
    ▼
Route (auth.routes.ts)
    │
    ▼
Middleware Chain
  ├── validate.middleware.ts   (Zod schema guard)
  ├── auth.middleware.ts       (JWT verification)
  └── rbac.middleware.ts       (role guard)
    │
    ▼
Controller (auth.controller.ts)
  └── Thin layer: parse request, call service, return response
    │
    ▼
Service (auth.service.ts)
  └── Business logic, orchestration, no DB concerns
    │
    ▼
Repository (auth.repository.ts)
  └── Pure data access layer — Mongoose queries only
    │
    ▼
Mongoose Model → MongoDB
```

**Key principles:**
- **Controller** never touches Mongoose directly
- **Service** never imports `req`/`res`
- **Repository** returns raw DB documents, service maps to DTOs
- **asyncHandler** wraps all controllers — eliminates try/catch boilerplate
- **Global error middleware** is the single point of failure formatting

---

## 3. Frontend Architecture

### Layered data flow

```
Zustand (auth state, user role)
        │
        ▼
React Query (server state — leads, pagination)
        │
        ▼
Axios Instance (interceptors → attach JWT, refresh on 401)
        │
        ▼
API Layer (leads.api.ts, auth.api.ts)
        │
        ▼
Custom Hooks (useLeads, useCreateLead…)
        │
        ▼
Page Components (LeadsPage)
        │
        ▼
UI Components (LeadTable, LeadFilters, Pagination…)
```

**Key principles:**
- **No direct Axios calls in components** — always via custom hooks
- **React Query** owns all server state; components never `useState` for API data
- **Zustand** owns only client-only global state (auth token, current user, theme)
- **Zod schemas** are single source of truth for form types (inferred with `z.infer<>`)
- **usePermissions** hook abstracts RBAC — no role checks scattered in JSX

---

## 4. Database Schema Design

### User Model

```typescript
interface IUser {
  _id: ObjectId;
  name: string;
  email: string;           // unique, indexed
  password: string;        // bcrypt hash
  role: 'admin' | 'sales';
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
}
```

### Lead Model

```typescript
interface ILead {
  _id: ObjectId;
  name: string;
  email: string;           // unique, indexed
  status: LeadStatus;      // indexed
  source: LeadSource;      // indexed
  notes?: string;
  assignedTo?: ObjectId;   // ref: User (future-ready)
  createdBy: ObjectId;     // ref: User
  createdAt: Date;         // indexed (for sort)
  updatedAt: Date;
}

type LeadStatus = 'new' | 'contacted' | 'qualified' | 'lost';
type LeadSource = 'website' | 'instagram' | 'referral';
```

**Mongoose Index Strategy:**
```typescript
LeadSchema.index({ status: 1 });
LeadSchema.index({ source: 1 });
LeadSchema.index({ createdAt: -1 });
LeadSchema.index({ name: 'text', email: 'text' }); // Full-text search
```

