## 5. API Design

### Base URL: `/api/v1`

#### Auth Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Body | Auth | Description |
|--------|----------|------|------|-------------|
| POST | `/auth/register` | `{name, email, password, role}` | None | Register user |
| POST | `/auth/login` | `{email, password}` | None | Login, get JWT |
| GET | `/auth/me` | — | JWT | Get current user |

#### Leads Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint | Query Params | Auth | RBAC |
|--------|----------|--------------|------|------|
| GET | `/leads` | `status, source, search, sort, page, limit` | JWT | Admin + Sales |
| GET | `/leads/:id` | — | JWT | Admin + Sales |
| POST | `/leads` | — | JWT | Admin + Sales |
| PUT | `/leads/:id` | — | JWT | Admin (full) / Sales (status only) |
| DELETE | `/leads/:id` | — | JWT | Admin only |
| GET | `/leads/export/csv` | `status, source, search` | JWT | Admin only |

#### Standard Response Envelope

```typescript
// Success
{
  "success": true,
  "message": "Leads retrieved successfully",
  "data": Lead[],
  "pagination": {
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 10,
    "total": 50,
    "pages": 5
  }
}

// Error
{
  "success": false,
  "message": "Unauthorized",
  "errors": [{ "field": "email", "message": "Invalid email" }]  // optional
}
```

---

## 6. Authentication Flow

```
1. Register
   POST /auth/register
   → Validate body with Zod
   → Check duplicate email
   → Hash password (bcrypt, saltRounds=12)
   → Save user to DB
   → Sign JWT (payload: { userId, role }, exp: 7d)
   → Return token + user object

2. Login
   POST /auth/login
   → Validate body
   → Find user by email
   → bcrypt.compare(plainPassword, hashedPassword)
   → Sign JWT
   → Return token + user object

3. Protected Request
   Any /leads/* request
   → Extract Bearer token from Authorization header
   → jwt.verify(token, JWT_SECRET)
   → Attach { userId, role } to req.user
   → Pass to next middleware

4. Frontend Token Lifecycle
   → On login: store JWT in Zustand (memory) + localStorage (persistence)
   → Axios interceptor: inject `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on every request
   → On 401 response: clear store → redirect to /login
   → On page refresh: rehydrate Zustand from localStorage
```

---

## 7. RBAC Flow

### Middleware Factory Pattern

```typescript
// Usage in routes:
router.delete('/:id', authenticate, authorize('admin'), controller.deleteLead);
router.put('/:id',    authenticate, authorize('admin', 'sales'), controller.updateLead);
```

### Permission Matrix

| Action | Admin | Sales |
|--------|:-----:|:-----:|
| View all leads | ✅ | ✅ |
| Create lead | ✅ | ✅ |
| Update lead (full) | ✅ | ❌ |
| Update lead status | ✅ | ✅ |
| Delete lead | ✅ | ❌ |
| Export CSV | ✅ | ❌ |

### Service-Level Field Guard (Sales Update)
```typescript
// In lead.service.ts
if (user.role === 'sales') {
  // Strip everything except `status` from the update payload
  const { status } = updateDto;
  return this.leadRepository.updateById(id, { status });
}
return this.leadRepository.updateById(id, updateDto);
```

### Frontend RBAC Hook
```typescript
// hooks/usePermissions.ts
const { can } = usePermissions();
{can('delete:lead') && <DeleteButton />}
```

---

## 8. Filtering + Pagination Strategy

### Backend Query Builder (in Repository)

```typescript
// All filters composed into a single Mongoose query object
const filter: FilterQuery<ILead> = {};

if (status) filter.status = status;
if (source) filter.source = source;
if (search) filter.$text = { $search: search };  // uses text index

const sortOrder = sort === 'oldest' ? 1 : -1;

const [leads, total] = await Promise.all([
  Lead.find(filter)
    .sort({ createdAt: sortOrder })
    .skip((page - 1) * limit)
    .limit(limit)
    .lean(),
  Lead.countDocuments(filter),
]);
```

### Query Parameter Contract
```
GET /api/v1/leads?status=qualified&source=instagram&search=rahul&sort=latest&page=2&limit=10
```

### Frontend Filter State (React Query key strategy)
```typescript
// Query key includes all filters → auto-refetch on filter change
const queryKey = ['leads', { status, source, search, sort, page }];
useQuery({ queryKey, queryFn: () => leadsApi.getLeads(filters) });
```

### Debounce Strategy
```typescript
// hooks/useDebounce.ts — 350ms delay on search input
const debouncedSearch = useDebounce(searchInput, 350);
// Passed into query key, so request only fires after user stops typing
```

